---
description: GitHub workflow enforcement (issue-first, branch-first)
alwaysApply: true
---

# Required Workflow

- For any non-trivial change, follow: **Issue → Branch → Validate → Commit → Push → PR**.
- Non-trivial = any app/runtime, dependency, CI/build/deploy, migration, posting/subledger/GL change, or >3 files (excluding docs/metadata-only edits).
- Branch naming: `feature/<issue>-<topic>`, `fix/<issue>-<topic>`, `chore/<issue>-<topic>`, `docs/<issue>-<topic>`, `refactor/<issue>-<topic>`, `test/<issue>-<topic>`.
- PR must include: linked issue, summary, exact validation commands, migration/data impact, financial-risk notes, rollback notes, UI screenshots if applicable.

# Safety Rules

- Never commit unless explicitly requested.
- Never push unless explicitly requested.
- Never force-push `main`.
- Direct-to-`main` only for tiny docs/metadata edits and only when explicitly requested.